wifi: mt76: mt7996: harden NULL pointer checks in TX/RX paths

Three NULL pointer dereference fixes:

1. mt7996_mac_tx_free(): Add wcid validation after mt76_wcid_ptr().
   The WLAN_ID from firmware TX free event can reference a station
   that was already freed. Without this check, wcid_to_sta() and
   subsequent rcu_dereference(sta->link[]) crash with a NULL deref
   in NAPI RX poll context.

2. mt7996_mac_sta_poll(): Add msta validation after extracting from
   poll_list. If a station is removed between being added to the
   poll list and being polled, msta_link->sta can be NULL.

3. mt7996_tx_prepare_skb(): Add missing NULL check for sta pointer
   before accessing sta->mlo in the EAPOL frame translation path.

These fixes address intermittent kernel crashes under sustained
high throughput reported in openwrt/openwrt#19638.

Signed-off-by: mingfai <ma@mingf.ai>
---
--- a/mt7996/mac.c
+++ b/mt7996/mac.c
@@ -114,6 +114,9 @@
 		list_del_init(&wcid->poll_list);
 		spin_unlock_bh(&dev->mt76.sta_poll_lock);

+		if (!msta || !wcid->sta)
+			continue;
+
 		idx = wcid->idx;

 		/* refresh peer's airtime reporting */
@@ -1060,7 +1063,7 @@
 	 * compatible with 802.11 EAPOL frame, we do the translation by
 	 * software
 	 */
-	if (tx_info->skb->protocol == cpu_to_be16(ETH_P_PAE) && sta->mlo) {
+	if (tx_info->skb->protocol == cpu_to_be16(ETH_P_PAE) && sta && sta->mlo) {
 		struct ieee80211_hdr *hdr = (void *)tx_info->skb->data;
 		struct ieee80211_bss_conf *link_conf;
 		struct ieee80211_link_sta *link_sta;
@@ -1328,6 +1331,10 @@

 			idx = FIELD_GET(MT_TXFREE_INFO_WLAN_ID, info);
 			wcid = mt76_wcid_ptr(dev, idx);
+			if (!wcid || !wcid->sta) {
+				link_sta = NULL;
+				goto next;
+			}
 			sta = wcid_to_sta(wcid);
 			if (!sta) {
 				link_sta = NULL;
